Lady Justice Martha Koome will on Friday that's a day away be sworn in as the country's 15 chief justice. President Uhuru Kenyatta has formally appointed her to the position after her nomination was approved by the national assembly. Members of parliament were full of praise for Kenya's first female chief justice with many affirming her fitness as head of the judiciary and that she won't bow to the whims of the executive. And as jeff Kirui reports, lady justice Koome takes charge at a time the judiciary and the executive are at loggerheads